\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4.42}{\ignorespaces Per-loop latency breakdown of \texttt {softmax} ($\texttt {MAXSIZE} = 16$) at \SI {150}{\mega \hertz }. The \texttt {exp} and \texttt {norm} loops report trip count~1 because \texttt {UNROLL factor=16} on a 16-element loop collapses all iterations into a single parallel pipeline stage.}}{56}{table.caption.401}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4.43}{\ignorespaces Timing summary for \texttt {softmax\_kvint8\_top} at the \SI {150}{\mega \hertz } target clock. The estimated path of \SI {5.084}{\nano \second } plus the \SI {1.800}{\nano \second } uncertainty exceeds the \SI {6.667}{\nano \second } budget by \SI {0.217}{\nano \second }, constituting a timing violation.}}{58}{table.caption.405}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4.44}{\ignorespaces Per-loop latency breakdown of the iteration~3 \texttt {softmax} ($\texttt {MAXSIZE} = 16$) at \SI {150}{\mega \hertz }. The \texttt {sum} loop collapses to a single effective iteration (trip count~1) due to the \texttt {UNROLL factor=16}, but its total latency increases from 97 to 185 cycles compared to iteration~1.}}{59}{table.caption.406}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4.45}{\ignorespaces Resource utilisation comparison between the iteration~1 baseline and the iteration~3 \texttt {softmax} designs, both at $\texttt {MAXSIZE} = 16$ on the ZCU102. Core figures exclude the AXI adapter and S-AXILite control interface.}}{59}{table.caption.407}%
