\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5.1}{\ignorespaces Timing summary for the \texttt {forward()} kernel at the \SI {150}{\mega \hertz } target clock. The estimated path of \SI {7.456}{\nano \second } plus \SI {1.800}{\nano \second } uncertainty exceeds the \SI {6.667}{\nano \second } budget by \SI {2.589}{\nano \second }.}}{103}{table.caption.723}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5.2}{\ignorespaces Resource utilisation of the \texttt {forward()} kernel after HLS synthesis on the ZCU102. Core-only figures exclude the four AXI master adapters. The \texttt {gmem0} adapter consumes 30\,BRAM, 881\,FF, and 1{,}052\,LUT. The \texttt {gmem1}--\texttt {gmem3} adapters each consume 4\,BRAM, 512\,FF, and 580\,LUT.}}{103}{table.caption.724}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5.3}{\ignorespaces Resource utilisation of the key synthesised submodule instances within the \texttt {forward()} kernel.}}{104}{table.caption.725}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5.4}{\ignorespaces Top-level latency summary for the \texttt {forward()} kernel at the \SI {150}{\mega \hertz } target clock. The minimum corresponds to \texttt {pos\,=\,0} (one attended position per head) and the maximum to \texttt {pos\,=\,2047} (full context length).}}{105}{table.caption.727}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5.5}{\ignorespaces Per-operation latency for one transformer layer at \SI {150}{\mega \hertz }. The Q projection uses a dedicated \texttt {matmul\_2048\_2048\_s} instance since its output dimension equals \texttt {dim}. The K and V projections share a \texttt {matmul\_2048\_256\_s} instance, as their output dimension equals \texttt {kv\_dim\,=\,256} under GQA. The gate and up projections share one \texttt {matmul\_2048\_5632\_s} instance, called sequentially.}}{105}{table.caption.728}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5.6}{\ignorespaces C-simulation results for all kernel primitives at both prototype and full TinyLlama scale. Tolerance values indicate the per-element absolute error threshold. Zero-error results indicate bit-identical outputs between the kernel and the software reference.}}{106}{table.caption.731}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5.7}{\ignorespaces End-to-end relative error between the \texttt {forward()} kernel and the float software reference across five token positions. Relative error is computed as total absolute difference divided by total reference magnitude, expressed as a percentage.}}{107}{table.caption.733}%
\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5.8}{\ignorespaces Theoretical inference throughput derived from HLS synthesis latency estimates at \SI {150}{\mega \hertz }. These figures assume the timing violation is resolved and the design operates at the target frequency. No hardware deployment measurements are available.}}{108}{table.caption.735}%
